I forgot that the fix for issue #12 is not included in style.qss but applied conditionally at runtime when you load the stylesheet. The python package provides a function to load the stylesheet which takes care of that but, in C++ it's up to you to add the missing extra stylesheet. e.g:

```cpp
QString loadStyleSheet()
{
    QFile f(":qdarkstyle/style.qss");
    QString stylesheet;
    if (!f.exists()) {
        printf("Unable to set stylesheet, file not found\n");
    } else {
        f.open(QFile::ReadOnly | QFile::Text);
        QTextStream ts(&f);
        stylesheet = ts.readAll();
#ifdef Q_OS_MACX
        stylesheet += "QDockWidget::title"
        "{"
        "    background-color: #353434;"
        "    text-align: center;"
        "}";
#endif
    }
    return stylesheet;
}
```

