OK, before we merge this I have one small item: currently if you `pipenv install --pre` or `pipenv install somepackage --pre` we simply run `project.update_settings({'allow_prereleases': pre})` -- Similarly, we should simply do this in `cli.py` so that when we query it later we have access to accurate info. 

As it stands with your changes, `pipenv lock --pre` won't ever generate a lockfile with prereleases in it unless it was previously set in the Pipfile.  

